args:
Dragonyule has come, and friends of all
types gather at the Halidom for a fun-filled
party. For his part in putting together this
snowy miracle—as well as everything else
he's done—the prince receives a surprise
present from all of his many friends.
Here's to another safely smited fiend.\nNow we can all stuff our faces in peace!
We got no way to say thanks 'cept for\nmere words, but them'll have to do.\nThanks a million!
This is all due to the hard work of everyone\nin the castle who culled the fiends and\nprepped for the party.
I owe them my thanks as well.
No need to thank me, darling!\nYou know I'd do anything for you!
I'm claiming the spot beside you!\nLet's make this a sweet evening\nto remember.
Er, right... Anyway, I hope you all enjoy it!
I ain't seen such a goldurn big Yuletree\nin all m'days!
And look at all the presents underneath it!\nHow exciting this all is!
Jeanne? What are you doing in the corner?
You should mingle with everyone and let\nthem see your fabulous dress.
I've...never been at an event like this.\nIn truth, I'm not sure how to behave.
Heh. Just start with enjoying yourself.\nCome on—we'll do it together.
Everyone bend the knee and accept the\ncharity of your king, Saint Starfall!
Prithee take this gift, fair child.\nI pray you might treasure it always.
It looks like adults and children alike are\nenjoying the festivities.
This has been a truly joyous day.
You seem happy, Cleo. I'm glad.
Being able to spend such a wonderful day\nwith you fills me with joy.
It's only so wonderful because of\nall the hard work everyone put into\npreparing for it.
No. This is all because of you.
A day of heartfelt celebration surmounting\nall of our various cultures? This is nothing\nshort of a miracle.
One that has been brought about because\nyou are who you are.
That's an exaggeration, don't you think?
I thought you might say that.
But we want you to understand just how\ngrateful we are, so we all pitched in and\ngot you a little something.
Your king bestows upon you a fine gift!
We made it for you ourselves.
It is a gift from all of us to you.
These folks will totally soft sell it,\nbut that puppy was a LOT of work!
We even went off into unexplored regions\nto find some of the materials—and it was\nall for you, darling!
I will even deign permit the awarding of a\ncrown to a vassal this one time, given\nthat this is the eve of Dragonyule.
Huh?! Yer the one who suggested a crown\nin the first place, ya chump!
Hold your tongue, churl! Hmph!\nOh, but in any case, don't be too\noverly satisfied with that gift.
That crown is proof of our faith in you,\nand also a reminder of your mission.
You wish to become the king of this\nland, do you not?
You will receive a true crown once you\ntake control of the continent.
But for now, you must make do with this.
I don't have to ＂make do＂ with it.\nThis makes me truly happy.
I'll cherish it forever—and I'll show you\nthat I am deserving of your faith.
I won't forget what happened here today.\nThank you all for the best Dragonyule ever!
We should do this again next year when\nall of us have grown even more.
And I will lead the way in that.
I'm going to make this kingdom\ngreat—a place where everyone\ncan live in peace and happiness.
I swear it on my crown.
